17:00 Doors open, pizza, drinks and mingle üçï

## ‚Äã**Talk 1: Resilient Security Operations**

‚ÄãSecurity operations aim to answer three core questions: where, how, and when an incident occurred. Yet, the default response is often to collect excessive logs and alerts, leading to noise, fatigue, and slow response times. This talk presents a clearer approach: centralizing security-relevant data, across identity, endpoints, cloud, and applications, and turning it into actionable insight that can be automated for faster and cheaper response. You‚Äôll leave with a practical understanding of SIEM and SOAR: what they are, why they matter, and how to use them to build more resilient, scalable security operations.
*Alex L√∂fstrand @ Irori*

## ‚Äã**Talk 2: Secure infrastructure**

‚ÄãFocusing on the layers beneath SIEM & SOAR, we cover how we securely provision, access, and manage the systems where detection and response occur. Using tools like Terraform, Vault, and Boundary, we‚Äôll explore how to automate secure deployments, manage secrets, and enforce least-privilege access across cloud environments.

Dive into the cutting-edge features of Oracle APEX and discover how to seamlessly integrate AI with your business data, simplifying and supercharging your app development process.

Engage with Oracle experts through live demos and interactive sessions that spotlight the latest APEX innovations.

(The agenda may be subjected to change)

**In person event only!**

8.30-9.00 Coffee

**9.00-9.10 Welcome**
*Mathias Magnusson, Leader of SWEOUG*

**9.15-10.00 APEX & AI: A complete overview**
*Menno Hoogendijk*
Oracle is now an AI company, even Oracle CloudWorld is now Oracle AI World. This session covers the vision of AI in APEX. Learn how can it be leveraged it today and in the future by you as developer and your end users.

**10.05-10.50 Cutting Through the Noise: AI-Powered Tender Management**
*Kai Donato*
Tender processes are slow and complex. Our APEX prototype uses AI and OCR to cut through the noise‚Äîextracting key data and enabling smart analysis with ChatGPT. The result: faster decisions, lower costs, and a smoother user experience. I‚Äôll share where today‚Äôs AI shines, where it struggles, and what‚Äôs next.

**10.50-11.00 Short Break**

**11.00-11.45 APEX New Features: Part 1**
*Menno Hoogendijk*
In this session we‚Äôll walk through many of the latest features and enhancements. Discover how awesome ideas from the community make their way into the product. Learn how these features simplify app development.

**11.45-12.30 Lunch**

**12.30-13.15 APEX New Features: Part 2**
*Fanel Secara*
In part 2 we‚Äôll uncover even more exciting new features! What is happening with APEX and AI? Let‚Äôs also put the spotlight on some hidden gems.

**13.25-14.10 How to prevent fraud in your Oracle database**
*G√∂ran Paues, Tradedoubler and SWEOUG*
Detecting suspicious activity early in your data is crucial to prevent fraud in your business. This talk explores how in-database machine learning algorithms can be used to detect anomalies. We will create a step-by-step SQL-based workflow to train and use a model for fraud detection on a sample dataset. Oracle Machine Learning for SQL (OML4SQL) will be used, and Oracle APEX will show graphs of the results.

**14.10-14.50 Coffee**

**14.50-15.35 Beyond Connectivity: Making APEX Work Offline**
*Kai Donato*
In addition to the many qualities of APEX, there is one feature that has not yet been supported: offline capability.

For this reason, developers have so far refrained from creating APEX pages that can be used without an active connection.
However, after several customer projects with precisely this requirement, we have now come to the conclusion that it is indeed possible to make an APEX application offline-capable using appropriate means.

**15.40-16.25 TBD**
*TBD - Local Speaker - Want to speak? Contact Mathias*

**16.25-16.30 Wrap up**
